<item>
            <title>[LU-7528] sanity test_160b test_160c tests defect: changelog user is not deregistered on test failure</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7528</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The test 160b and 160c of sanity does not deregister the changelog users that they have registered so if tests which run &quot;changelog_register&quot; fails before &quot;changelog_deregister $USER&quot;, then &quot;changelog_deregister $USER&quot; never gets executed and all changes (such as file creation, deletion, etc.) are still recorded. This can be the reason why tests stdouts are huge, they contain &quot;lfs changelog lustre-MDT0000&quot; results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example : &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;test_160b () {
...
    USER=$(do_facet $SINGLEMDS $LCTL --device $MDT0 changelog_register -n)
...
    touch $LONGNAME1 || error &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;create of $LONGNAME1 failed&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
...
    echo &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;deregistering $USER&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    do_facet $SINGLEMDS $LCTL --device $MDT0 changelog_deregister $USER
...
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>single node, 4-node</environment>
